DESEF ‚Äî Operations Cycle
Purpose:
Maintain orientation, prevent drift, and ensure DESEF remains a navigator firm, not an operator.

0. Daily Prime (5‚Äì10 min)
‚òê What phase is DESEF in today?
‚òê What phase is each engagement in?
‚òê Where is authority currently concentrated?
‚òê Is anything becoming irreversible?

If unclear ‚Üí halt execution ‚Üí return to orientation.

1. Weekly Cycle (Canonical)
Monday ‚Äî Orientation & Load
Intent: Re-establish coherence before action.

‚òê Review active engagements
‚òê Re-confirm phase per engagement
‚òê Identify authority bleed or dependency
‚òê Check personal / firm load
‚òê Decide: Proceed / Pause / Kill

Output:

Updated phase annotations

Explicit go / no-go list

Wednesday ‚Äî Design & System Health
Intent: Improve systems, not momentum.

‚òê Review architectures / OS artifacts
‚òê Validate authority stacks (Resource ‚Üí Legitimacy)
‚òê Check pilot boundaries and kill criteria
‚òê Audit AI/tool permissions
‚òê Update risk register (lightweight)

Output:

Design deltas

Risk updates

Constraint clarifications

Friday ‚Äî Exit Pressure
Intent: Force removal of DESEF from systems.

‚òê Where is DESEF still ‚Äúholding the system up‚Äù?
‚òê What knowledge can be transferred this week?
‚òê What access can be revoked?
‚òê What can be closed, archived, or terminated?
‚òê What should not continue next week?

Output:

Exit actions

Terminations / graduations

Reduced dependency

2. Engagement Lifecycle Loop (Per System)
Phase 0 ‚Äî Orientation
‚òê System mapped
‚òê Authority identified
‚òê Constraints explicit
‚òê Non-commitment maintained

Phase 1 ‚Äî Design
‚òê Architecture defined
‚òê Governance modeled
‚òê OS / kernel specified
‚òê Reversibility confirmed

Phase 2 ‚Äî Pilot
‚òê Pilot bounded
‚òê Signals defined
‚òê Kill criteria armed
‚òê Observation > intervention

Phase 3 ‚Äî Transfer
‚òê Knowledge transferred
‚òê Authority reassigned
‚òê DESEF access removed
‚òê Exit acknowledged

If Phase 3 stalls ‚Üí system is unhealthy

3. Monthly Reset (Once per Month)
‚òê Are we executing too much?
‚òê Is Phase 0 being skipped?
‚òê Is DESEF becoming indispensable anywhere?
‚òê Are exits actually happening?
‚òê Is the firm still light, legible, and optional?

Decision:
‚òê Continue as-is
‚òê Reduce scope
‚òê Pause intake
‚òê Reset operations

4. Firm Health Dashboard (Manual Check)
‚òê Too many simultaneous engagements
‚òê Founder identity hardening
‚òê Execution pressure rising
‚òê Orientation time shrinking
‚òê Exit conversations avoided

‚â•2 checked ‚Üí initiate pause protocol

5. Pause Protocol (Immediate)
‚òê Stop new commitments
‚òê Freeze pilots
‚òê Communicate pause externally
‚òê Re-enter orientation
‚òê Decide what not to resume

6. Termination Protocol (Clean Kill)
‚òê Reason documented
‚òê Dependencies mapped
‚òê Access revoked
‚òê Artifacts archived
‚òê Closure acknowledged

Termination is a successful outcome.

7. Canonical Operating Rules
Orientation precedes execution

Phase discipline is mandatory

Authority must be explicit

Irreversibility is failure

Exit is success

8. End-of-Week Reflection (2 min)
‚òê Did DESEF reduce its footprint this week?
‚òê Did any system become healthier without us?
‚òê What should stop now?

