DESEF ‚Äî Firm Cycle
Purpose:
Ensure DESEF remains a systems-engineering navigator firm‚Äîlight, reversible, phase-aware, and non-permanent.

1. Firm State (Single Source of Truth)
Current Firm State:
‚òê Orienting
‚òê Designing
‚òê Piloting
‚òê Transferring
‚òê Paused
‚òê Dormant

State Start Date:
Next Mandatory Review Date:

Only one firm state may be active at a time.

2. Firm Cycle (Authoritative)
State 0 ‚Äî Orientation (Default)
Intent: Decide whether DESEF should act at all.

‚òê Re-establish mission
‚òê Review system landscape
‚òê Identify legitimate demand
‚òê Confirm personal capacity
‚òê Decide what not to do

Exit Conditions:
‚òê Clear design mandate exists
‚òê Authority boundaries agreed
‚òê Reversibility confirmed

State 1 ‚Äî Design
Intent: Convert orientation into coherent system designs.

‚òê Architect systems / OS / regimes
‚òê Define authority stacks
‚òê Specify constraints and limits
‚òê Design exits in advance

Prohibitions:

No scaling

No long-term commitments

No operational ownership

Exit Conditions:
‚òê Design stable
‚òê Pilot boundaries defined
‚òê Kill criteria armed

State 2 ‚Äî Pilot
Intent: Learn, not succeed.

‚òê Run bounded pilots
‚òê Observe system behavior
‚òê Capture failure modes
‚òê Avoid heroics

Non-Negotiables:
‚òê Timeboxed
‚òê Budget capped
‚òê Explicit kill switch

Exit Conditions:
‚òê Hypothesis resolved
‚òê System terminated or graduated

State 3 ‚Äî Transfer
Intent: Remove DESEF from the system.

‚òê Transfer knowledge
‚òê Reassign authority
‚òê Revoke DESEF access
‚òê Confirm independence

Completion Signal:
‚òê System operates without DESEF

State 4 ‚Äî Pause
Intent: Prevent institutional harm.

Triggers:
‚òê Load too high
‚òê Founder dependency forming
‚òê Phase discipline eroding
‚òê Personal capacity compromised

Actions:
‚òê Freeze intake
‚òê Halt pilots
‚òê Communicate pause
‚òê Re-orient

State 5 ‚Äî Dormancy
Intent: DESEF exists only as a legal and intellectual shell.

‚òê No active engagements
‚òê No operational authority
‚òê Knowledge archived

Dormancy is a valid success state.

3. Transition Rules (Non-Negotiable)
Orientation ‚Üí Design requires explicit consent

Design ‚Üí Pilot requires kill criteria

Pilot ‚Üí Transfer or Termination only

Any state ‚Üí Pause at any time

Dormancy may follow any state

4. Firm Intake Gate (Must Pass)
‚òê System-level problem (not product ask)
‚òê Authority holder identified
‚òê Exit accepted upfront
‚òê Phase 0 honored
‚òê DESEF not required long-term

If any unchecked ‚Üí reject or defer

5. Firm Load Limits
Max Concurrent Engagements:
Max Active Pilots:

‚òê Load exceeded ‚Üí auto-pause

6. Drift Detection
‚òê DESEF becoming operator
‚òê Founder centrality increasing
‚òê Execution rewarded over orientation
‚òê Exit conversations delayed

If ‚â•2 ‚Üí immediate Pause

7. Termination Doctrine
‚òê Termination ‚â† failure
‚òê Silence is not consent
‚òê Clean exits preserve legitimacy
‚òê No sunk-cost exceptions

8. Weekly Firm Review (5 min)
‚òê Is current firm state still correct?
‚òê Should DESEF transition states?
‚òê What can be removed or ended?

9. Canonical Firm Law
DESEF is temporary by design

Authority must be explicit

Reversibility is mandatory

Exit is success

Orientation precedes action

