DESEF ‚Äî Portfolio Cycle
Purpose:
Maintain a healthy, bounded portfolio of systems while preventing overload, founder dependency, and phase collapse.

1. Portfolio Snapshot (Single View)
Portfolio State:
‚òê Light
‚òê Stable
‚òê Loaded
‚òê Overloaded
‚òê Paused

Portfolio Review Date:
Next Mandatory Review:

Portfolio State overrides individual engagement urgency.

2. Portfolio Composition (Manual Table)
System / Engagement	Phase	Risk	Dependency on DESEF	Status
Low / Med / High	Low / Med / High	Active / Paused / Exiting
Rules:

No more than 2 High-Dependency systems at once

Any High Risk + High Dependency ‚Üí pause portfolio intake

3. Canonical Portfolio Cycle
Stage 0 ‚Äî Intake (Gatekeeping)
Intent: Prevent bad systems from entering the portfolio.

‚òê System-level problem (not product request)
‚òê Authority holder identified
‚òê Exit accepted upfront
‚òê Phase 0 honored
‚òê Portfolio capacity available

Fail any ‚Üí reject or defer

Stage 1 ‚Äî Orientation (Portfolio-Scoped)
Intent: Understand how this system changes the portfolio, not just itself.

‚òê System mapped
‚òê Portfolio impact assessed
‚òê Dependency risk estimated
‚òê Redundancy checked

Key Question:

Does this system crowd out something more important?

Stage 2 ‚Äî Design
Intent: Design systems to minimize long-term portfolio drag.

‚òê Authority stack explicit
‚òê Exit path designed
‚òê Knowledge transfer planned
‚òê Pilot boundaries defined

Portfolio Rule:
No more than N designs without exits in motion.

Stage 3 ‚Äî Pilot
Intent: Learn quickly without portfolio destabilization.

‚òê Pilot timeboxed
‚òê Kill criteria armed
‚òê Portfolio load monitored
‚òê No new pilots if portfolio is ‚ÄúLoaded‚Äù

Automatic Triggers:

Pilot overrun ‚Üí portfolio review

Dependency spike ‚Üí pause pilot

Stage 4 ‚Äî Transfer or Termination
Intent: Reduce portfolio weight.

‚òê Knowledge transferred
‚òê Authority reassigned
‚òê DESEF access revoked
‚òê System archived or graduated

Graduation reduces portfolio load
Termination also reduces portfolio load

4. Portfolio Load Limits (Set Once)
Max Active Systems:

Max Active Pilots:

Max High-Dependency Systems:

‚òê Any limit breached ‚Üí auto-pause intake

5. Drift & Concentration Detection
‚òê Too many systems in same phase
‚òê Too many systems relying on Navigator
‚òê Old systems not exiting
‚òê Portfolio feels ‚Äúheavy‚Äù

‚â•2 checked ‚Üí portfolio reset

6. Portfolio Reset Protocol
‚òê Freeze intake
