üßæ 5) TAX ATTRIBUTION ‚Äî ENTITY & MEMBER
Cooperative Entity (Combined 1120-C Logic)
A) SUMMARIZE REVENUE
Item	Amount
Patronage Income	$943,000
Non-Patronage Income	$557,000
Total Revenue	$1,500,000
B) 1120-C TAXABLE INCOME CALCULATION
Under Subchapter T (U.S. coop tax law), patronage distributions are deductible when properly documented and allocated:

Taxable Income = Total Revenue ‚àí Patronage Distributions
               = $1,500,000 ‚àí $943,000
               = $557,000
Entity Tax Due (example at 21% corporate rate):

$557,000 √ó 21% ‚âà $116,970
(Taxes vary by jurisdiction and entity status; this is a simulation.)

üìÑ 6) MEMBER TAX SUMMARIES
