May also have honorarium or stipend

Council D
Patronage Income: $83,927

Stipends if any are ordinary income

Apprentice E
Patronage Income: $104,685

Taxed as ordinary income

üìã 7) SPREADSHEET LOGIC (COPY-ABLE)
SHEET: Revenue & Patronage
A	B	C	D	E
Entity	Revenue	Patronage %	Patronage Income	Non-Patronage Income
DESEF	300000	0.8	=B2*C2	=B2-D2
OVCS	250000	0.7	=B3*C3	=B3-D3
Kumba	180000	0.6	=B4*C4	=B4-D4
Ventures	420000	0.5	=B5*C5	=B5-D5
Platforms	350000	0.6	=B6*C6	=B6-D6
Totals	=SUM(B2:B6)	‚Äî	=SUM(D2:D6)	=SUM(E2:E6)
SHEET: CU Allocation
A	B	C	D	E
Member	CUs	Total CUs	CU %	Allocation (e.g. DESEF)
Worker A	120	450	=B2/C2	=D2 * (DESEF $240000)
Steward B	180	450	=B3/C3	=D3 * (DESEF $240000)
Board C	60	450	=B4/C4	=D4 * (DESEF $240000)
Council D	40	450	=B5/C5	=D5 * (DESEF $240000)
Apprentice E	50	450	=B6/C6	=D6 * (DESEF $240000)
SHEET: Member Tax Summary
A	B	C	D
Member	Total Patronage Income	Other Compensation	Total Taxable Income
Worker A	=SUM(DESEF alloc, OVCS alloc, ‚Ä¶)	[salary cell]	=B2 + C2
Steward B	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶
Board C	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶
Council D	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶
Apprentice E	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶	‚Ä¶
üîç KEY TAX INSIGHTS
‚úî Members are taxed on patronage distributions as ordinary income (Form 1099-PATR).
‚úî The cooperative entity deducts patronage distributions and pays tax only on non-patronage income (Form 1120-C).
‚úî This avoids double taxation for most of the coop‚Äôs income.
‚úî Members at higher marginal rates may owe significant tax on large patronage allocations.

