8. Kernel Firm Reality Check
A kernel firm must have:

the right to say no to its creator

the right to shut things down

the right to remain small

the right to starve ventures of legitimacy

Capital-originated entities cannot do this credibly.

Kernels must be pre-capital or parallel to capital, never downstream of it.

