PART II ‚Äî SIMULATION: MEMBER DEMANDS MORE AUTHORITY
Scenario
H2 (Systems Analyst) requests authority to ‚Äúdecide which ventures should proceed‚Äù because they ‚Äúunderstand the system best.‚Äù

Step-by-Step Response (By Design)
Immediate Boundary Flag

P2 (DESEF Lead) logs an authority overreach

No debate on merit

Written Justification Required

H2 must submit rationale citing charter language

There is none ‚Üí request invalid

Navigator Estate Review

P5 confirms pattern or one-off

Logged in system memory

Corrective Action

Authority request denied

Responsibilities clarified in writing

If Repeated

Escalation to Board (B1)

Removal without stigma (‚Äúrole mismatch‚Äù)

Key Insight
No one argues whether H2 is right.
The system only checks whether H2 is allowed.

This prevents slow coups.

PART III ‚Äî VESTING + EXIT CLAUSES (ALIGNED TO RACI)
A. VESTING PRINCIPLES (UNIVERSAL)
