I. OVERVIEW: LEGAL OWNERSHIP + COMPENSATION PRINCIPLES
Before we get to specifics, here are the core rules that govern everything:

1) Ownership Is Functional, Not Financial
Across the federation:

Equity/ownership rights are tied to role and contribution.

No one ‚Äúowns‚Äù the entire system as a profit-seeking asset.

Each legal entity has its own ownership & compensatory model, consistent with its legal form (cooperative, non-profit, LLC, etc.).

2) No Capital-Capture Sort of Equity
Capital (OVCS LPs, external investors) cannot hold controlling equity.

External investors get non-voting shares or capped returns, never governance.

Capital cannot influence upstream layers (Umoya, DESEF, Navigator).

3) Compensation Is Aligned with Contribution, Not Hierarchy
Worker cooperatives: compensation based on work & value created.

Stewardship roles: compensated for service & burden, not ownership.

Board & Council seats: stipends or honoraria, not equity.

4) Entities Have Distinct Legal/Ownership Models
Each layer uses the legal form that best enforces its boundary:

Entity	Legal Type	Ownership Logic	Compensation Form
Umoya Society	Non-profit / Trust	No financial ownership	Program fees, stipends, grants
Navigator Estate	Non-profit cooperative	No financial upside	Honoraria / stewardship fees
DESEF	Worker Cooperative	Worker & Steward equity	Profit sharing via coop
Kumba Franchise Units	Franchise coops	Local worker equity	Local profit sharing
OVCS	Cooperative LLC or Venture Studio Co-op	Non-voting shares	Management fees, carry (capped)
12 Ventures	Worker Cooperatives	Worker & OVCS non-voting	Profit sharing
7 Platforms	Commons Cooperative	Commons shares	Usage fees, grants
II. OWNERSHIP & COMPENSATION ‚Äî ENTITY BY ENTITY
1) UMOYA SOCIETY (KUZU)
Legal Form: Non-profit corporation or charitable trust
Ownership:

No equity; mission held by trust

Programs governed by membership and charter
Compensation:

Facilitators, program staff ‚Äî salaried/stipends

Honoraria for contributors

All surplus reinvested in mission

Key Legal Structure:

501(c)(3) in U.S. or equivalent elsewhere

Board fiduciary duties to mission, not profit

2) NAVIGATOR ESTATE
Legal Form: Non-profit cooperative (mutual benefit)
Ownership:

No financial equity

‚ÄúStewardship shares‚Äù symbolizing custodial rights
Compensation:

Honoraria, expense reimbursements

Compensation tied to service periods

Not based on venture/platform returns

Legal Purpose:

Maintain continuity, memory, boundary enforcement

3) DESEF (Dominic Eaton Systems Engineering Firm)
Legal Form: Worker Cooperative Corporation
Ownership:

Worker equity: Members own controllable shares

Steward equity: Partners (Domain Stewards) hold separate class of non-voting oversight shares

Founder equity: Decays over time into Steward equity to prevent capture

Compensation:

Salary + profit sharing based on hours/contribution

End-of-year surplus distributed per coop rules

No performance bonuses tied to venture outcomes

Legal Protections:

Partner (steward) shares cannot be traded or sold

Cooperative bylaws require supermajority for external capital

4) KUMBA META-FACTORY (Franchise Units)
Legal Form: Network of worker cooperatives + central standards IP trust
Ownership:

Each Kumba unit owned by its workers

Central Kumba IP held in a common trust (not equity)

Compensation:

Local worker salaries and profit share

Franchise standard fees (capped, periodic)

Legal Requirement:

Franchise agreements require adherence to coop principles

5) OVCS (Obatala Venture Capital Studios)
Legal Form: Cooperative Studio LLC or Multi-Stakeholder Coop
Ownership:

Internal members: Studio operators have equity

External capital: Investors get non-voting economic interests (unit trust shares) with capped returns

Coop governance always retains veto power

Compensation:

Management fees on ventures

Capped carry on exits

Surplus beyond caps flows back into coop/public commons

Guardrails (Legal):

Investor rights agreement restricts governance influence

Cooperative bylaws require coop votes for capital activation

6) 12 VENTURES
Legal Form: Worker Cooperatives or Social Enterprise Coops (specific to mission)
Ownership:

Worker-members: majority voting equity

OVCS economic units: non-voting, capped return shares

Federation oversight share: golden share with veto on capture

Compensation:

Salaries based on role & output

Profit distributions per cooperative rules

Investor Rights:

External capital limited to non-voting, capped instruments (e.g., repayable grants, revenue share capped return notes)

7) 7 PLATFORMS (Commons/Infrastructure)
Legal Form: Cooperative Commons Entities
Ownership:

Shared ‚ÄúCommons Shares‚Äù representing usage rights

No personal financial equity

Compensation:

Staff/stewards salaried by platform usage/licensing revenues

Surplus reinvested in platform sustainability

Rights:

Usage rights assigned by coop agreements

No transfer of equity to private owners

III. OWNERSHIP RIGHTS BY MEMBER CLASS
Below is how legal ownership and financial benefit map to each role category:

Class A ‚Äî Founding Steward Members
Ownership:

Steward equity in DESEF

Symbolic roles in Navigator Estate
Compensation:

Honoraria (Estate), profit share (DESEF only)
Restrictions:

Cannot control ventures or capital

