Template 1 ‚Äî Worker Cooperative Member Agreement
(Draft ‚Äî to be adapted by counsel in your jurisdiction)

WORKER COOPERATIVE MEMBER AGREEMENT
This Worker Cooperative Member Agreement (‚ÄúAgreement‚Äù) is entered into as of [Date], by and between [Cooperative Name], a worker cooperative organized under the laws of [Jurisdiction] (‚ÄúCooperative‚Äù), and [Member Name] (‚ÄúMember‚Äù).

1. PURPOSE
The purpose of this Agreement is to set forth the terms under which the Member shall participate in the Cooperative, including rights, responsibilities, equity interests, compensation, and exit provisions.

2. DEFINITIONS
‚ÄúMember Equity‚Äù means the ownership interest granted to the Member under the Cooperative‚Äôs bylaws.
‚ÄúProfit Share‚Äù means the Member‚Äôs share of surplus distributed in accordance with the Profit Sharing Policy.

3. MEMBERSHIP REQUIREMENTS
3.1 Role & Duties.
Member agrees to fulfill responsibilities of the role of [Role Title] as defined in the Cooperative‚Äôs governance documents.

3.2 Compliance.
Member agrees to abide by the Cooperative Bylaws, Member Handbook, and any policies adopted by the Cooperative.

4. EQUITY INTEREST
4.1 Equity Grant.
Subject to the Cooperative‚Äôs vesting policy, Member will be granted [Number/% of Shares/Units] of Member Equity.

4.2 Vesting.
Equity vests according to the Cooperative‚Äôs Vesting Policy attached as Exhibit A.

4.3 Non-Transferability.
Member Equity is non-transferable except as permitted in the Cooperative‚Äôs bylaws.

5. COMPENSATION
5.1 Base Compensation.
Member will be paid a base salary or wage pursuant to the Cooperative‚Äôs compensation structure.

5.2 Profit Sharing.
Member will participate in profit sharing in accordance with the Cooperative‚Äôs Profit Sharing Policy.

5.3 Benefits.
Member is eligible for benefits as described in the Cooperative‚Äôs benefit policies.

6. TERMINATION & EXIT
6.1 Voluntary Exit.
Member may withdraw from membership upon 30 days‚Äô written notice and following the Cooperative‚Äôs exit procedures.

6.2 Involuntary Termination.
Member may be terminated for cause in accordance with Cooperative policies.

6.3 Equity Treatment on Exit.
Unvested equity returns to the Cooperative; vested equity is handled per the Vesting and Exit Policy.

7. CONFIDENTIALITY
Member agrees to maintain the confidentiality of proprietary and sensitive Cooperative information.

8. GOVERNING LAW
This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of [Jurisdiction].

IN WITNESS WHEREOF‚Ä¶
[Cooperative Name]

By: _______________________
Name: _____________________
Title: ____________________

Member

By: _______________________
Name: _____________________
Date: _____________________

