1Ô∏è‚É£ WORKER COOPERATIVE MEMBER AGREEMENT
(USA-oriented general template)

----------------------------------------------
WORKER COOPERATIVE MEMBER AGREEMENT
----------------------------------------------

This Agreement (‚ÄúAgreement‚Äù) is entered into on [Date], between [Cooperative Name], a worker cooperative organized under [State] Cooperative Law (‚ÄúCooperative‚Äù), and [Member Name], (‚ÄúMember‚Äù).

1. PURPOSE
The Member agrees to participate in the Cooperative, contributing labor and abiding by the Cooperative‚Äôs bylaws and policies.

2. DEFINITIONS
‚ÄúMember Equity‚Äù means the ownership interest granted to the Member as described in the Cooperative‚Äôs bylaws.

3. MEMBERSHIP
3.1 Member agrees to fulfill duties as outlined in role descriptions.
3.2 Member must follow Cooperative bylaws and policies.

4. EQUITY GRANT
4.1 Member is granted [#/%] of Member Equity subject to vesting under the Cooperative‚Äôs Vesting Policy.
4.2 Vesting occurs according to the attached Vesting Policy.

5. NON-TRANSFERABILITY
Member Equity is non-transferable except as permitted by bylaws.

6. COMPENSATION
6.1 Member receives base compensation per Cooperative compensation structure.
6.2 Member participates in profit sharing per Cooperative Profit Sharing Policy.

7. EXIT
7.1 Member may withdraw upon written notice per bylaws.
7.2 Unvested equity returns to Cooperative; vested equity treated per Exit Policy.

8. CONFIDENTIALITY
Member shall keep proprietary information confidential.

9. GOVERNING LAW
This Agreement is governed by the laws of [State].

IN WITNESS WHEREOF:
[Cooperative]      __________________________
Member             __________________________
2Ô∏è‚É£ OVCS INVESTOR NON-VOTING UNIT CONTRACT
----------------------------------------------
OVCS INVESTOR NON-VOTING UNIT AGREEMENT
----------------------------------------------

This Agreement is between [OVCS Name], a Cooperative LLC (‚ÄúOVCS‚Äù), and Investor [Name].

1. PURPOSE
Investor purchases non-voting units (‚ÄúUnits‚Äù) in OVCS with capped return rights.

2. UNITS
2.1 Units do not confer governance or voting rights.
2.2 Units entitle the Investor to economic return capped at [X%] of invested capital.

3. DISTRIBUTIONS
3.1 OVCS will distribute returns when available after Cooperative obligations.
3.2 No right to distributions beyond cap.

4. TRANSFER RESTRICTIONS
4.1 Units are non-transferable except under approved secondary market rules.

5. NO GOVERNANCE RIGHTS
Investor has no right to vote or direct OVCS operations.

6. TERM & EXIT
6.1 Units remain until repurchase by OVCS or maturity.
6.2 Repurchase occurs at cap or fair market valuation if greater.

7. CONFIDENTIALITY & COMPLIANCE
Investor agrees to confidentiality and compliance with law.

8. GOVERNING LAW
This Agreement governed by [State] law.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF:
OVCS            ________________________
Investor        ________________________
3Ô∏è‚É£ NAVIGATOR ESTATE STEWARDSHIP CHARTER
----------------------------------------------
NAVIGATOR ESTATE STEWARDSHIP CHARTER
----------------------------------------------

1. PURPOSE
The Navigator Estate preserves constitutional continuity, system memory, and boundary enforcement across the Cooperative Federation.

2. STEWARDSHIP ROLE
Stewards hold custodial authority, not executive authority.

3. NOMINATION & APPOINTMENT
3.1 Stewards are appointed by constitutional process.
3.2 Terms are [X] years with a max of [Y] consecutive terms.

4. DUTIES
4.1 Monitor systemic drift.
4.2 Archive institutional memory.
4.3 Trigger constitutional reviews as needed.

5. COMPENSATION
Stewards receive honoraria; no profit share or equity.

6. LIMITS
Stewards shall not execute operations or control entities.

7. TERM & EXIT
Stewards may resign; exit triggers transfer of stewardship to new appointee.

8. AMENDMENT
Charter amendments require supermajority of Steward votes.

9. GOVERNING LAW
This Charter governed by [State] law.
4Ô∏è‚É£ PROFIT SHARING & VESTING POLICY
----------------------------------------------
PROFIT SHARING & VESTING POLICY
----------------------------------------------

1. PURPOSE
Defines how profit is shared among member categories and how equity vests.

2. PROFIT SHARING
2.1 Profit defined as surplus after expenses, reserves, and obligations.
2.2 Distribution hierarchy:
   a) Operational reserves
   b) Worker compensation
   c) Profit share pool
2.3 Worker members receive allocation based on hours/contribution.

3. VESTING SCHEDULE
3.1 Equity vests over [4] years with a 1-year cliff.
3.2 Vesting pauses upon leave > [X] days.

4. EXIT TREATMENT
4.1 Unvested equity forfeited to the Cooperative.
4.2 Vested equity repurchased at book value or formula in bylaws.

5. NON-TRANSFERABILITY
Equity cannot be transferred except by exit terms.

6. GOVERNANCE
Policy adopted by Cooperative board and binding on members.

7. LAW
Policy governed by [State] law.
