üî• When Does CUMULATIVE REVENUE Reach $1 B?
Under these projections:

üü¢ High Scenario
By end of Year 13‚Äì15 (estimated) system cumulative revenue passes $1B
(based on continuing the aggressive growth curve ~40‚Äì50% CAGR beyond Year 10)

üü° Medium Scenario
Likely crosses $1B cumulative around Year 16‚Äì18

üî¥ Low Scenario
Unlikely to reach $1B cumulative within 20 years without acceleration
(revenue would need a breakout vector ‚Äî e.g., a venture becomes breakout SaaS)

Note: These projections assume continuation of the trend beyond Year 10 similarly.
If a venture achieves viral adoption, cumulative revenue can accelerate much faster (see ‚ÄúAggressive Growth‚Äù projection earlier).

üìä Sensitivity Insights
Sensitivity to Key Drivers
Driver	Low	Medium	High
Platform Adoption	Slow	Moderate	Fast
Venture Success	Modest	Some scaling	Significant scaling
Grants / Public Funding	Dependent	Stable	Strategic increases
Capital Influence	Minimal	Controlled	Managed but growth-friendly
Most Impactful Levers
Platform revenue velocity ‚Äî increases recurring revenue

Venture breakout hits ‚Äî can spike medium and high projections

Franchise node expansion ‚Äî multiplies Kumba revenue

Contract and consulting growth ‚Äî stabilizes DESEF revenue

üìå Summary
Total Headcount Growth (Y1 ‚Üí Y5)
From ~27 to ~68 total functional roles (full + fractional)

Burn & Cash Flow
Low scenario breakeven early Y2

Medium Y2 with solid surplus by Y5

High positive from Year 2

Cumulative Revenue
Low: ~$81M by Year 10

