ividends** ‚Äì paid annually on surplus - **Equity Redemption** ‚Äì when a member exits - **Commons Returns** ‚Äì reinvested or purpose-used - **OVCS Share** ‚Äì limited carry/fee portion --- ## A. WORKER DIVIDENDS (AGGREGATE) Using Base Case Surplus: | Year | Surplus | Commons 15% | Worker Pool 50% | Retained | |------|---------|-------------|-----------------|----------| | 1 | 0.6M | 90k | 300k | 210k | | 2 | 1.8M | 270k | 900k | 630k | | 3 | 3.0M | 450k | 1.5M | 1.05M | | 4 | 4.8M | 720k | 2.4M | 1.68M | | 5 | 7.0M | 1.05M | 3.5M | 2.45M | **Worker dividend pool** grows with scale; typical per head depends on member count. --- ## B. EQUITY REDEMPTION (EXIT) Members redeem equity according to formula: ``` Equity Value = (Accumulated Surplus per Member √ó Vesting %) ``` Sample: - A member exiting Year 3 with vested 20% of units might redeem ~$85k √ó 20% = **~$17k** --- ## C. OVCS STUDIO SHARE OVCS receives a capped *studio share* of surplus (e.g., 15%). These are **NOT control rights**, only revenue share. --- ### STUDIO SHARE TRACKING (Base Case) | Year | Surplus | OVCS Share (15%) | |------|---------|------------------| | 1 | 0.6M | 90,000 | | 2 | 1.8M | 270,000 | | 3 | 3.0M | 450,000 | | 4 | 4.8M | 720,000 | | 5 | 7.0M | 1,050,000 | These flows can be: - Recycled to coops - Used to back new ventures - Part of reserves --- # V. HOW TO USE THESE MODELS ### In Practice: 1. **Load into a spreadsheet** - Each scenario (Best, Base, Worst) in separate tabs 2. **Run sensitivity tests** - Churn ¬±10% - Growth ¬±10‚Äì30% - Tax treatments ¬±change 3. **Monitor key ratios** - Surplus per member - Surplus/Revenue % - Runway for each entity 4. **Simulate shocks** - Revenue dips - cost spikes - member exits --- # VI. WHAT THIS REVEALS ‚úî You achieve **positive unit economics quickly** ‚úî Cooperative surplus can fund growth and redistribute value ‚úî Membership churn is **manageable and net-positive** ‚úî Capital returns exist but **do not centralize control** ‚úî Your system