NDEBE answers: ‚ÄúHow do people stay together without institutions?‚Äù

ZAMBA ‚Äî material interface (but not yet production)
Important distinction:
ZAMBA here is not factories yet.

It is:

value flows

labor patterns

exchange logic

proto-economic forms

ZAMBA answers: ‚ÄúHow does value move without capture?‚Äù

Why this does make more sense early
1. It avoids premature centers
No OVCS ‚Üí no ‚Äúengine‚Äù
No DESEF ‚Üí no kernel
No ventures ‚Üí no performance pressure
No platforms ‚Üí no standardization risk

You are laying conditions, not structures.

2. It reduces founder gravity
You are not ‚Äúrunning‚Äù anything.
You are publishing fragments.

People can:

use them

ignore them

misinterpret them

That‚Äôs ideal early.

3. It creates optionality later
If this stack is solid:

Umoya can emerge from it

OVCS can adopt it without owning it

Kuzu can operate within it

DESEF can be one kernel among many

You are no longer forced to defend coherence.

