Be honest about the cost.

You lose:
speed to production

economic proof

visible traction

leverage with partners

ability to ‚Äúdo everything in Year-1‚Äù

This is a slow legitimacy path.

The real tradeoff (this is the key)
You are choosing between:

Path A ‚Äî Entity-first
‚ÄúWe are building things; trust us.‚Äù

Requires:

constant restraint

constant refusal

continuous firebreak maintenance

High risk, high output.

Path B ‚Äî Substrate-first
‚ÄúHere are patterns; do with them what you will.‚Äù

Requires:

patience

tolerance of ambiguity

comfort with invisibility

Lower risk, lower immediate output.

