1. THE LEGAL PRIMITIVES (WHAT THE LAW ACTUALLY SEES)
You are not inventing new law.
You are composing existing legal forms in a constrained way.

Across the system, there are only five legal primitives:

Individual natural persons

Cooperative corporations (worker coops, multi-stakeholder coops)

Nonprofit / public-benefit entities

For-profit corporations or LLCs

Trusts (including commons / purpose trusts)

Everything else is contractual overlay.

