3. MEMBER CLASSES: OWNERSHIP + COMPENSATION BY CLASS
This answers your question directly.

CLASS A ‚Äî WORKER-MEMBERS (HIRES, OPERATORS)
Legal Status
Employees and cooperative members

Governed by state cooperative statutes (e.g., CA Worker Coop Act, ICA model)

Ownership
Hold membership shares in:

their venture coop

their platform guild

or Kumba local coop

Shares:

Non-speculative

Non-transferable outside the coop

Redeemable on exit at book value or formula value

Compensation
Wages / salary (W-2 or equivalent)

Patronage dividends (profit share, taxed as income)

Vested membership equity (redeemable, not tradable)

They do not own:

Umoya

DESEF as a whole

OVCS centrally

Commons Capital

CLASS B ‚Äî STEWARD-MEMBERS (PARTNERS)
Legal Status
Members of the CCF

Not employees

Not directors

Ownership
Hold stewardship equity units:

non-controlling

non-transferable

vest over time

convertible only to economic rights, not votes

They do not own:

ventures

platforms

IP

commons assets

Compensation
Stipend or retainer (1099 / contractor)

Long-term surplus participation (if any)

No upside tied to exits

This avoids:

shadow management

incentive to centralize

CLASS C ‚Äî GOVERNANCE MEMBERS (BOARD)
Legal Status
Directors or trustees (depending on entity)

Fiduciary duty holders

Ownership
None

Explicitly prohibited from equity

Compensation
Fixed stipend

Expense reimbursement only

No bonuses.
No carry.
No upside.

This is legally clean and standard in public-benefit governance.

CLASS D ‚Äî COMMONS / COUNCIL MEMBERS
Legal Status
Advisors / fellows / community representatives

Ownership
None

Compensation
Honoraria

Expense coverage

No financial upside

This preserves voice without capture.

CLASS E ‚Äî FOUNDER-MEMBER (NAVIGATOR)
Legal Status
Individual

Member of CCF

Possibly beneficiary (not owner) of Trust

Ownership
Holds:

founder equity units (time-bounded)

vested interests in some ventures (if working there)

Does not own Commons Capital

Does not own Umoya

Founder equity:

Cannot expand

Cannot convert into control

Sunsets per charter

Compensation
Salary (if operational)

Dividends (like any other vested member)

No perpetual royalty

No founder tax

Legally enforceable via charter + contracts.

