So you get internal mobility ‚Äî people move from venture to platform or to program roles.

IV. CAPITAL RETURN FOOTPRINTS
This models how capital comes back to participants over time without breaking cooperative constraints.

MODEL COMPONENTS
Worker Dividends ‚Äì paid annually on surplus

Equity Redemption ‚Äì when a member exits

Commons Returns ‚Äì reinvested or purpose-used

OVCS Share ‚Äì limited carry/fee portion

A. WORKER DIVIDENDS (AGGREGATE)
Using Base Case Surplus:

Year	Surplus	Commons 15%	Worker Pool 50%	Retained
1	0.6M	90k	300k	210k
2	1.8M	270k	900k	630k
3	3.0M	450k	1.5M	1.05M
4	4.8M	720k	2.4M	1.68M
5	7.0M	1.05M	3.5M	2.45M
Worker dividend pool grows with scale; typical per head depends on member count.

B. EQUITY REDEMPTION (EXIT)
Members redeem equity according to formula:

Equity Value = (Accumulated Surplus per Member √ó Vesting %)
Sample:

A member exiting Year 3 with vested 20% of units might redeem ~$85k √ó 20% = ~$17k

C. OVCS STUDIO SHARE
OVCS receives a capped studio share of surplus (e.g., 15%). These are NOT control rights, only revenue share.

STUDIO SHARE TRACKING (Base Case)
Year	Surplus	OVCS Share (15%)
1	0.6M	90,000
2	1.8M	270,000
3	3.0M	450,000
4	4.8M	720,000
5	7.0M	1,050,000
These flows can be:

Recycled to coops

